race.description: Amh Auto Group Moruya Country Magic Showcase Hcp
race.comment: SHE WITHIN (5) talented mare unlucky not to have a few more wins on the CV. Returned excellent closing splits when third over 1100m at Rosehill in Highway grade on November 29. Kept up to the mark with an 800m trial win at Goulburn and ticks plenty of boxes. LIQUOR TALK (11) also comes out of Highway company after racing without luck. Faded late when no match for the progressive Mount Bona over 1500m at Rosehill. Kept fresh and look for him late. CYCLONE RUPERT (1) battled away late on resumption when an even fifth over 1200m at Goulburn in this grade. Proven second-up and likely to go back from the gate. MISS SCOOP (7) smart on her day and on the backup over the preferred trip. Griped on late when fourth over 1000m at Wagga. Well placed to bounce back.
